  "text": "Japanese food is healthy. You've heard that. What you haven't heard? Sashimi has zero fiber. Zero. But Japan also gave us edamame, natto, burdock root, things that are actually fiber bombs. Edamame alone, eight grams per cup. That's more than most protein bars claiming to be healthy. Natto is weirder. Fermented soybeans. Tastes like an acquired taste. Five grams of fiber per serving. Worth it. Burdock root, six grams per half cup. Most people have never touched it. The Japanese gut health secret isn't sushi. It's the stuff nobody orders. The recipes are at dailylifehacks.com. Free. In your inbox. Weekly.",
